# ERP Report Template & Branding Standard

## Phase

```
REPORT.2 — Global Report Engine + Registry + Security Foundation (2026-06-19)
```

---

## Rules

### 1. All branding must resolve from erp_report_branding_profiles.

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
const branding = await resolveReportBranding({ ownerCompanyIds, registryEntry });

// ❌ Never — inline company branding
const logoUrl = "https://cdn.algt.net/logo.png";
const companyName = "Alliance Gulf";
```

### 2. Template seeding convention for new companies.

When a new owner company is created, seed:
```sql
COMPANY_{id}_DEFAULT         -- erp_report_branding_profiles
COMPANY_{id}_REPORT_TEMPLATE -- erp_report_templates
COMPANY_{id}_LETTER_TEMPLATE -- erp_report_templates
```

Then update:
```sql
owner_companies.default_report_template_id
owner_companies.default_letter_template_id
```

### 3. Template types and their correct usage.

| Type | Correct Use | Wrong Use |
|---|---|---|
| `report` | Data lists, summaries | Letters or certificates |
| `letter` | Employee letters, HR notifications | Data reports |
| `certificate` | Training cert, employment cert | List reports |
| `badge` | ID badge, access card | Data reports |
| `group_summary` | Multi-company consolidated | Single company report |

### 4. Stamp and signature fields require reports.sign permission.

```typescript
// Template flag
requires_stamp_permission: true

// Caller must have
callerPermissionCodes.includes('reports.sign')

// If permission missing, stamp_url and signature_url must NOT be exposed
```

### 5. Never create branding profiles with hardcoded company-specific names.

```typescript
// ❌ Never
profile_code: 'ALGT_BRANDING'
profile_name: 'Alliance Gulf Transport Branding'

// ✅ Correct — use dynamic company-based code
profile_code: `COMPANY_${ownerCompanyId}_DEFAULT`
profile_name: `${company.legal_name_en} — Default`
```

### 6. Language mode rules.

| Mode | When to use |
|---|---|
| `en` | English-only output |
| `ar` | Arabic-only output (RTL) |
| `bilingual` | Side-by-side EN+AR on same page |

Bilingual mode is only supported in REPORT.3+ (requires template renderer upgrade).

### 7. Custom CSS must be minimal and safe.

- `custom_css` in `erp_report_templates` is for minor layout overrides only.
- Must not inject `<script>`, `eval()`, or external `@import` rules.
- Applied server-side only by the PDF renderer (REPORT.3+).

